------ the barin of the spring---------
A dependency is simply a class that another class needs.

example: car needs engine => engine = dependency of car

--------------------------------
dependency injection
-----------------------------
Objects are created and provided by a framework
instead of creating them manually.
--------------------------------------
Before DI:

Car → creates Engine
---------------------------------------
After DI:

Spring → creates Engine
Spring → injects Engine into Car

Developer does not write new Engine().
------------------
this framework automaticalky 
1. creates objects
2. manages their lifecycle
3. injcts dependencies
--------------------------------
1. Loose Coupling
Classes are independent.

2. Easy Testing
You can replace dependencies with mocks.

3. Easy Maintenance
Changing one component doesn't break the whole system.